</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=setch>Setch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/10/02 10:49:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=676.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: no lures</span><hr size=1> Aye and I respect that.<br>
And I'm aware of mod rod mk 2, and how delicious they are, though I've yet to taste one myself =)<br>
<br>
And I understand that mages have it rough. But I just don't think lure spells for mages are the answer. It is a wizard specialty and I can't help but feel a little defensive about it =)<br>
<br>
I have a gut feeling that increasing your nuking power is never going to properly compensate for broken pets and a spotty summons list. You already know what the problems are, and how they need to be fixed. No matter how blind verant has been to you, you're selling yourself short if you give up and try to accomodate their poor judgement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uburrowowlx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>burrowowlx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 12:52:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=676.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mage lures?</span><hr size=1> Quite frankly, at a 2:1 ratio, you want lures?  You got em.  Lures are worthless.  Ever since the big MR debuff of a few months ago, I think the only thing I have cast lure on was Tunare, but I might be misremembering.  Other than that, I haven't cast them once.  I suspect that if you are getting nasty resist rates, you probably just need to level.<br>
<br>
I don't want mages to have lures because I don't want anyone to have lures.  They are a stupid hack.  Int casters should do more damage than over armored tanks, and lures are not the answer to that.<br>
<br>
For that matter, you want dragonbane?  It's all yours.<br>
<br>
Manastorm &gt; Tears of Druzzil &gt; porlos fury on every dragon it lands on.  Which, IIRC, is every dragon save one that porlos hits.<br>
<br>
Necros were whining about lures about a year ago (actually, they may still be whining about them.)  You are more than welcome to lures.  You will find yourself woefully disappointed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udamoens.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damoen S</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 4:40:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=676.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mage Lures</span><hr size=1> Mages I feel your pain.<br>
<br>
And yes I know what it feels like to be highly resisted.  Lures do help, but they are not the cure.  I also disagree with the Mages getting the stone spell your talking about.  But not because it would unbalance Mages.  But because once mages got the spell Mobs would also.  And most likely the mobs would get an AE version of the spell.  <br>
<br>
On Raids If I could find a mage that would cast their Malo line of spells I would have a new best friend.  Problem is all the mages/necros/shaman that I have been raiding with have all forgotten about their debuffs.  Therefore reducing my damage ablility as well.  From what I have noticed while fighting without debuffs I average about 60-75% of my max fighting power.  With debuffs I am alot closer to 90%.<br>
<br>
You know as well as I do what VI will say.  &quot;Since Mages can't use their pets on raids, they still have debuffs, DSs and nukes.  Therefore they are still balanced.  We like the idea that mages have to change their style of play during raids.&quot;  Now if in game the balance is true does not seem to matter to them.  I think they only look at such things on paper.  Oh how I hope caster balance brings some changes, big changes.  I really hope Mages and Wizards benifit from these changes not just the triad.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Moderator</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Verant's #1 Fanboy</font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 5:37:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=676.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mage Lures</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The problem is we OFTEN CANNOT USE PETS!!<br>
<br>
Where can mages generally NOT use pets? RAIDS. Please do not tell me we can, because generally we CAN'T (I have used pets everywhere bar TOV and ST, I know what I'm doing and I STILL can't or won't use pets in many raids).<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
There's almost no situation where you can't use a pet, if you know how to control it.  Brodie, Fuedar, and Maltily (Mages in my guild obviously!) always have a pet up on every raid with the exception of Ssra when we're moving.  When we get to the boss we're there for they get them up.  We have never had a pet train us anywhere.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Where do we meet high resist mobs usually? On Raids, yes?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Nope, not anymore.  At least on a majority of the mobs.  Obviously before the resist change patch went in there were problems, but since then it's virtually non-exhistant.  I know because I always try my trusty rend robe (mr based nuke) on every mob we fight.  Rend lands almost every single time.  Besides boss mobs fire and magic nukes will land on almost every standard mob found in dungeons.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> How would YOU like it, as a wizard, if on a raid you are told &quot;Oh no nukes, O'Kiels the tanks, TL and port folk in and out.&quot; Would YOU be happy? That's the situation mages face, and I for one am rather *** about it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well, our job is nuking and dealing fast efficient damage.  Your job as a Mage is to provide damage and raid utility.  You can't have the best of both worlds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> mages, wizards and necros are the damage dealing Int casters, we've been screwed over for ages, I am merely proposing one way to help my class that's within reason. I don't mind the idea of mobs with high resists, I do object when we aren't given the means to affect them by using a different set of tools.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Check out the &quot;damage&quot; a Necromancer deals on raids, then come back here and see if that statement holds true.  Necros can only do extreme damage to mobs on long, drawn out fights... and at that they can only do it if there are 1-2 at the most there since their dots don't stack.<br>
<br>
Mages combat high resists with their pets which will hit anything.  See your pet as a lure-based DoT. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In any case one of the class defining skills of a Wizard next to quick hard damage was reliable damage (lures).  Personally I don't think anyone should have lures except Wizards and Abashi said awhile back that no one else would get lures but Wizards.  I wouldn't be totally against a level 60 Mage spell that did say.. 500 lure dmg for 350 mana or something.  <br>
<br>
Lastly you came here asking our opinion on what we thought about Mages getting lures and you got it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Don't get so upset when we say we don't like the idea.  I feel for you guys and I know you're not perfect but there are many other solutions than just giving Mages lure-based spells. <p><br>
